es © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by a Jewish captive who became the wife of the Persian king Ahasuerus. Her Hebrew name was <i>Hadassah</i> ‘myrtle’, and the form <i>Esther</i> is said to be a Persian translation of this, although others derive it from Persian <i>stara</i> ‘star’. It may also be a Hebrew form of the name of the Persian goddess <i>Ishtar</i>. According to the book of the Bible that bears her name, Esther managed, by her perception and persuasion, to save large numbers of the Jews from the evil machinations of the royal counsellor Haman.  See also  Hester ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":53,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Esther was born in 1402, in Devon, England. She had at least 1 daughter with William Martin. She died in 1467, in Combe Martin, Devon, England, at the age of 65."},"et":{"1402–1467":"1402–1467","1400–1470":"1400–1470","1422–1450":"1422–1450","1402":"1402","1467":"1467","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1450":"1450","after 1450":"pärast 1450","1470":"1470","Combe Martin, Devon, England":"Combe Martin, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"1402–1467":"1402–1467","1400–1470":"1400–1470","1422–1450":"1422–1450","1402":"1402","1467":"1467","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1450":"1450","after 1450":"1450 jälkeen","1470":"1470","Combe Martin, Devon, England":"Combe Martin, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"1402–14